<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910703-0114</DOCNO><DOCID>910703-0114.</DOCID><HL>   Destec Signs Power Agreement</HL><DATE>07/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   ENG ORU</CO><MS>UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   HOUSTON -- Destec Energy Inc. said it signed a powerpurchase agreement with Orange andamp; Rockland Utilities Inc. ofPearl River, N.Y., for electrical power to be produced by theNorthway cogeneration project, currently being developed byDestec in Harriman, N.Y. Terms weren't disclosed.   The Northway cogeneration project, scheduled to beginoperation in 1994, will be fueled by natural gas and isdesigned to provide up to 57 megawatts of electrical power tothe utilities and thermal energy for industrial use. Destecis currently negotiating fuel supply and transportationarrangements as well as the sale of steam.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>